uspended%20for%20declaring%20martial%20law%20last%20year.%20Mr%20Han%20was%20impeached%20by%20lawmakers%20in%20December%2C%20just%20weeks%20after%20he%20took%20over%20as%20acting%20leader%20from%20President%20Yoon%20Suk%20Yeol%2C%20who%20was%20himself%20impeached%20over%20his%20short-lived%20suspension%20of%20civilian%20legal%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Han's%20impeachment%20was%20dismissed%20in%20a%207-1%20vote%20by%20the%20court's%20eight%20justices.%20Two%20justices%20voted%20to%20reject%20the%20impeachment%20motion%20entirely%2C%20according%20to%20news%20agency%20Yonhap.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPrime%20Minister%20Han%20lasted%20less%20than%20two%20weeks%20in%20the%20post%20and%20was%20impeached%20and%20suspended%20on%20December%2027%20after%20clashing%20with%20the%20opposition-led%20parliament%20by%20refusing%20to%20appoint%20three%20more%20justices%20to%20the%20Constitutional%20Court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EParliament%20impeached%20him%20over%20his%20alleged%20role%20in%20martial%20law%2C%20as%20well%20as%20his%20refusal%20to%20appoint%20more%20justices%20and%20back%20special%20counsel%20bills%20targetting%20Yoon%20and%20First%20Lady%20Kim%20Keon%20Hee.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFinance%20Minister%20Choi%20Sang-mok%20assumed%20the%20position%20of%20acting%20president%20while%20the%20cases%20of%20Mr%20Yoon%20and%20Mr%20Han%20were%20considered%20by%20the%20Constitutional%20Court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EAbout%C2%A0Han%20Duck-soo%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Han%2C%2075%2C%20had%20served%20in%20leadership%20positions%20for%20more%20than%20three%20decades%20under%20five%20presidents%2C%20both%20conservative%20and%20liberal.%20In%20a%20country%20sharply%20divided%20by%20partisan%20rhetoric%2C%20he%20had%20been%20seen%20as%20a%20rare%20example%20of%20an%20official%20whose%20varied%20career%20transcended%20party%20lines.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20the%20opposition-led%20parliament%20accused%20him%20of%20not%20doing%20enough%20to%20thwart%20Yoon's%20decision%20to%20declare%20martial%20law%2C%20an%20accusation%20he%20denied.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Han%20attended%20the%20only%20hearing%20in%20the%20case%20on%20February%2019%2C%20where%20he%20denied%20any%20role%20in%20the%20martial%20law%20episode%20and%20called%20for%20the%20court%20to%20dismiss%20the%20impeachment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EMartial%20Law%20In%20South%20Korea%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20unexpected%20imposition%20of%20martial%20law%20on%20December%203%20by%20President%20Yoon%20and%20the%20ensuing%20political%20upheaval%20sent%20shockwaves%20through%20Asia's%20fourth-largest%20economy%20and%20drew%20concerns%20from%20allies%20such%20as%20the%20United%20States%20who%20had%20seen%20Yoon%20as%20a%20key%20partner%20in%20efforts%20to%20counter%20China%20and%20North%20Korea.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20martial%20law%20in%20the%20end%20only%20lasted%20about%20six%20hours%20after%20lawmakers%20voted%20to%20reject%20the%20declaration%2C%20after%20defying%20efforts%20by%20police%20and%20the%20military%20to%20seal%20off%20parliament%2C%20hopping%20fences%20to%20avoid%20the%20security%20cordons.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1742781000000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-12%2Fa8a3i25k_han-ducksoo_625x300_27_December_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fsouth-koreas-court-dismisses-impeachment-of-pm-han-duck-soo-over-martial-law-7995219%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22South%20Korea's%20Constitutional%20Court%20struck%20down%20the%20impeachment%20of%20Prime%20Minister%20Han%20Duck-soo%20on%20Monday%2C%20reinstating%20him%20as%20acting%20president--%20a%20role%20he%20was%20given%20after%20the%20president%20was%20suspended%20for%20declaring%20martial%20law%20last%20year.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fsouth-koreas-court-dismisses-impeachment-of-pm-han-duck-soo-over-martial-law-7995219%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl