3E%3Cli%3EPaul%20Weiss%20Chairman%20Brad%20Karp%20sent%20an%20email%20to%20employees%20on%20Sunday.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20email%20addressed%20the%20firm's%20deal%20with%20Trump%20after%20an%20executive%20order%20targeted%20it.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EKarp%20acknowledged%20that%20%26quot%3Bmany%26quot%3B%20employees%20are%20%26quot%3Buncomfortable%26quot%3B%20over%20the%20resolution.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EPaul%20Weiss%20Chairman%20Brad%20Karp%20knows%20some%20employees%20feel%20uneasy%20about%20the%20law%20firm's%20deal%20with%20the%20Trump%20administration.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20he%20sent%20an%20email.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPaul%20Weiss%20is%20among%20several%20major%20firms%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump-memo-orders-big-law-firms-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPresident%20Donald%20Trump%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20targeted%20this%20month%20with%20executive%20orders%20over%20their%20DEI%20policies%20and%20political%20affiliations.%20The%20orders%20revoked%20the%20security%20clearance%20of%20lawyers%20at%20Paul%20Weiss%20and%20called%20for%20the%20review%20of%20the%20firm's%20government%20contracts.%20The%20firm%20is%20associated%20with%20Trump's%20political%20rivals%2C%20including%20attorney%20Mark%20Pomerantz%2C%20who%20left%20the%20firm%20to%20join%20the%20Manhattan%20district%20attorney's%20investigation%20into%20Trump's%20finances.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20order%2C%20uncertainty%20gripped%20the%20law%20firm%20and%20it%20began%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpaul-weiss-law-dei-practices-trump-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elosing%20clients%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Then%2C%20Trump%20announced%20on%20Friday%20he%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpaul-weiss-law-dei-practices-trump-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereached%20a%20resolution%20with%20Paul%20Weiss%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20withdrew%20the%20executive%20order.%20The%20resolution%20included%20specific%20stipulations%2C%20including%20providing%20%2440%20million%20in%20pro%20bono%20services%20to%20the%20administration.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20deal%20shocked%20some%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frachel-cohen-harvard-lawyer-quit-big-law-trump-legal-fights-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elegal%20community%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20was%20alarmed%20by%20what%20some%20saw%20as%20a%20capitulation%20by%20the%20powerful%20firm.%20Karp%20attempted%20to%20address%20those%20concerns%20in%20an%20email%20to%20staffers%20on%20Sunday.%20The%20email%20was%20first%20reported%20by%20the%20legal%20publication%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdavidlat.substack.com%2Fp%2Fbrad-karp-firmwide-email-to-paul-weiss-about-the-trump-administration-deal%3Futm_source%3Dpost-email-title%26publication_id%3D229933%26post_id%3D159697336%26utm_campaign%3Demail-post-title%26isFreemail%3Dtrue%26r%3D3xbvei%26triedRedirect%3Dtrue%26utm_medium%3Demail%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOriginal%20Jurisdiction%3C%2Fa%3E.%20A%20Paul%20Weiss%20representative%20confirmed%20the%20contents%20of%20the%20email%20to%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20is%20a%20copy%20of%20the%20full%20email%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Csection%3ESubject%3A%20Statement%20to%20the%20PW%20Community%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EDear%20Members%20of%20the%20Paul%2C%20Weiss%20Community%2C%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EI%20wanted%20to%20take%20this%20opportunity%20to%20speak%20with%20all%20of%20you%20more%20fully%20about%20the%20events%20of%20recent%20days.%20I%20know%20that%20this%20has%20been%20a%20profoundly%20unsettling%20time%20for%20all%20of%20you.%20Information%20gaps%20have%20been%20filled%20with%20speculation%2C%20concern%2C%20and%20misinformation%2C%20and%20I%20wanted%20to%20take%20this%20opportunity%20to%20address%20your%20concerns%20directly.%20Thank%20you%20for%20taking%20the%20time%20to%20listen.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3ELate%20in%20the%20evening%20of%20Friday%2C%20March%2014%2C%20the%20President%20issued%20an%20executive%20order%20targeting%20our%20firm.%20Since%20then%2C%20we%20have%20been%20facing%20an%20unprecedented%20threat%20to%20our%20firm%20unlike%20anything%20since%20Samuel%20Weiss%20first%20hung%20out%20a%20shingle%20in%20downtown%20Manhattan%20on%20April%201%2C%201875%E2%80%94almost%20exactly%20150%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EOnly%20several%20days%20ago%2C%20our%20firm%20faced%20an%20existential%20crisis.%20The%20executive%20order%20could%20easily%20have%20destroyed%20our%20firm.%20It%20brought%20the%20full%20weight%20of%20the%20government%20down%20on%20our%20firm%2C%20our%20people%2C%20and%20our%20clients.%20In%20particular%2C%20it%20threatened%20our%20clients%20with%20the%20loss%20of%20their%20government%20contracts%2C%20and%20the%20loss%20of%20access%20to%20the%20government%2C%20if%20they%20continued%20to%20use%20the%20firm%20as%20their%20lawyers.%20And%20in%20an%20obvious%20effort%20to%20target%20all%20of%20you%20as%20well%20as%20the%20firm%2C%20it%20raised%20the%20specter%20that%20the%20government%20would%20not%20hire%20our%20employees.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EWe%20were%20hopeful%20that%20the%20legal%20industry%20would%20rally%20to%20our%20side%2C%20even%20though%20it%20had%20not%20done%20so%20in%20response%20to%20executive%20orders%20targeting%20other%20firms.%20We%20had%20tried%20to%20persuade%20other%20firms%20to%20come%20out%20in%20public%20support%20of%20Covington%20and%20Perkins%20Coie.%20And%20we%20waited%20for%20firms%20to%20support%20us%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20the%20President's%20executive%20order%20targeting%20Paul%2C%20Weiss.%20Disappointingly%2C%20far%20from%20support%2C%20we%20learned%20that%20certain%20other%20firms%20were%20seeking%20to%20exploit%20our%20vulnerabilities%20by%20aggressively%20soliciting%20our%20clients%20and%20recruiting%20our%20attorneys.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EWe%20initially%20prepared%20to%20challenge%20the%20executive%20order%20in%20court%2C%20and%20a%20team%20of%20Paul%2C%20Weiss%20attorneys%20prepared%20a%20lawsuit%20in%20the%20finest%20traditions%20of%20the%20firm.%20But%20it%20became%20clear%20that%2C%20even%20if%20we%20were%20successful%20in%20initially%20enjoining%20the%20executive%20order%20in%20litigation%2C%20it%20would%20not%20solve%20the%20fundamental%20problem%2C%20which%20was%20that%20clients%20perceived%20our%20firm%20as%20being%20persona%20non%20grata%20with%20the%20Administration.%20We%20could%20prevent%20the%20executive%20order%20from%20taking%20effect%2C%20but%20we%20couldn't%20erase%20it.%20Clients%20had%20told%20us%20that%20they%20were%20not%20going%20to%20be%20able%20to%20stay%20with%20us%2C%20even%20though%20they%20wanted%20to.%20It%20was%20very%20likely%20that%20our%20firm%20would%20not%20be%20able%20to%20survive%20a%20protracted%20dispute%20with%20the%20Administration.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20we%20learned%20that%20the%20Administration%20might%20be%20willing%20to%20reach%20a%20resolution%20with%20us.%20So%2C%20working%20with%20our%20outside%20counsel%2C%20we%20did%20exactly%20what%20we%20advise%20our%20clients%20to%20do%20in%20%26quot%3Bbet%20the%20company%26quot%3B%20litigation%20every%20day%3A%20we%20talked%20with%20the%20Administration%20to%20see%20if%20we%20could%20achieve%20a%20lasting%20settlement%20that%20would%20not%20require%20us%20to%20compromise%20our%20core%20values%20and%20fundamental%20principles.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EIn%20a%20matter%20of%20days%2C%20we%20were%20able%20to%20negotiate%20such%20a%20resolution.%20That%20resolution%2C%20the%20terms%20of%20which%20I%20shared%20with%20all%20of%20you%20on%20Thursday%20evening%2C%20had%20three%20primary%20components.%20First%2C%20we%20reiterated%20our%20commitment%20to%20viewpoint%20diversity%2C%20including%20in%20recruiting%20and%20in%20the%20intake%20of%20new%20matters.%20Second%2C%20while%20retaining%20our%20longstanding%20commitment%20to%20diversity%20in%20all%20of%20its%20forms%2C%20we%20agreed%20that%20we%20would%20follow%20the%20law%20with%20respect%20to%20our%20employment%20practices.%20And%20third%2C%20we%20agreed%20to%20commit%20%2410%20million%20per%20year%20over%20the%20next%20four%20years%20in%20pro%20bono%20time%20in%20three%20areas%20in%20which%20we%20are%20already%20doing%20significant%20work%3A%20assisting%20our%20Nation's%20veterans%2C%20countering%20anti-Semitism%2C%20and%20promoting%20the%20fairness%20of%20the%20justice%20system.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3ETo%20be%20clear%2C%20and%20to%20clarify%20misinformation%20perpetuated%20from%20various%20media%20sources%2C%20the%20Administration%20is%20not%20dictating%20what%20matters%20we%20take%20on%2C%20approving%20our%20matters%2C%20or%20anything%20like%20that.%20We%20obviously%20would%20not%2C%20and%20could%20not%20ethically%2C%20have%20agreed%20to%20that.%20Instead%2C%20we%20have%20agreed%20to%20commit%20substantial%20pro%20bono%20resources%2C%20in%20addition%20to%20the%20%24130%2B%20million%20we%20already%20commit%20annually%2C%20in%20areas%20of%20shared%20interest.%20We%20will%20continue%20all%20of%20the%20existing%20pro%20bono%20work%20we%20already%20do%20and%20will%20continue%20in%20our%20longstanding%20role%20as%20a%20leader%20of%20the%20private%20bar%20in%20the%20pro%20bono%20and%20public%20interest%20sphere.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EThis%20existential%20crisis%20required%20the%20leadership%20of%20our%20law%20firm%20to%20make%20incredibly%20difficult%20decisions%20under%20extraordinary%20time%20pressure.%20In%20making%20those%20decisions%2C%20we%20were%20guided%20by%20two%20fundamental%20principles.%20First%20and%20foremost%2C%20we%20were%20guided%20by%20our%20obligation%20to%20protect%20our%20clients'%20interests.%20As%20I%20mentioned%20earlier%2C%20we%20concluded%20that%20even%20a%20victory%20in%20litigation%20would%20not%20be%20sufficient%20to%20do%20so%2C%20because%20our%20firm%20would%20still%20be%20perceived%20as%20persona%20non%20grata%20with%20the%20Administration.%20We%20simply%20could%20not%20practice%20law%20in%20the%20Paul%2C%20Weiss%20way%20if%20we%20were%20still%20subject%20to%20the%20executive%20order.%20This%20resolution%20was%20unambiguously%20in%20our%20clients'%20best%20interests.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EEqually%20important%2C%20we%20were%20guided%20by%20our%20fiduciary%20duty%20to%20all%20of%20you%E2%80%94by%20our%20obligation%2C%20as%20stewards%20of%20the%20firm%2C%20to%20protect%20the%20livelihoods%20of%20the%202%2C500%20lawyers%20and%20non-legal%20professionals%20who%20work%20at%20Paul%2C%20Weiss.%20That%20consideration%E2%80%94the%20need%20to%20ensure%2C%20above%20all%2C%20that%20our%20firm%20would%20survive%E2%80%94weighed%20extremely%20heavily%20on%20all%20of%20us%2C%20and%20especially%20on%20me%2C%20as%20the%20leader%20of%20the%20firm.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EIn%20today's%20political%20environment%2C%20it%20is%20unsurprising%20that%20the%20announcement%20that%20we%20have%20negotiated%20a%20resolution%20with%20the%20Administration%2C%20rather%20than%20fighting%20it%20in%20court%2C%20has%20generated%20intense%20feelings%20across%20the%20firm%20and%20indeed%20across%20the%20entire%20legal%20and%20broader%20community.%20As%20is%20often%20the%20case%20in%20situations%20like%20this%2C%20the%20extensive%20media%20coverage%20and%20social%20media%20commentary%20surrounding%20recent%20events%20has%20taken%20on%20a%20life%20of%20its%20own%2C%20with%20its%20own%20factual%20narrative%20and%20its%20own%20momentum.%20The%20coverage%20has%20been%20decidedly%20unhelpful%2C%20piecemeal%2C%20and%20incorrect%20in%20many%20fundamental%20respects.%20But%20it%20is%20not%20particularly%20constructive%20for%20any%20of%20us%20involved%20to%20debate%20factual%20discrepancies.%20Instead%2C%20what%20is%20most%20important%20is%20to%20look%20to%20the%20future.%20In%20this%20regard%2C%20I%20want%20to%20provide%20some%20clarity%20and%20perspective%20as%20we%20move%20forward.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EFirst%2C%20an