20we'd%20had%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmiscarriage-grief-age-older-parent-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Emy%20last%20two%20pregnancies%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20sonographer%20flipped%20the%20monitor%20for%20us%20to%20see.%20%26quot%3BWe've%20got%20heartbeats%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere%20are%20three%20of%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224c11d25f-5cd0-4a29-9970-e1b3f32ec285%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20struggled%20with%20guilt%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWe%20planned%20that%20I'd%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fc-section-things-i-wished-i-knew-before-birth-2021-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ehave%20a%20C-section%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20with%2028%20doctors%20and%20nurses%20in%20the%20room%20%E2%80%94%20a%20team%20for%20me%20and%20a%20team%20for%20each%20of%20the%20babies.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAlthough%20I%20knew%20in%20advance%20that%20the%20babies%20would%20be%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnicu-doctor-shares-what-parents-nicu-babies-need-to-know-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Etaken%20straight%20to%20the%20NICU%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20I%20didn't%20realize%20how%20traumatic%20it%20would%20be%20to%20be%20separated%20from%20my%20babies.%20We'd%20been%20a%20team%20%E2%80%94%20the%20three%20of%20them%20in%20me%20%E2%80%94%20for%20months%2C%20and%20then%20they%20were%20just%20taken%20away.%20It%20felt%20so%20wrong.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20few%20days%20after%20they%20were%20born%2C%20two%20of%20my%20babies%20had%20to%20be%20moved%20to%20a%20different%20hospital%2C%20while%20the%20one%20other%20baby%20and%20I%20stayed%20in%20the%20original%20hospital.%20That%20was%20the%20worst%20day%20of%20my%20life.%20I%20just%20didn't%20imagine%20this%20would%20be%20my%20start%20to%20motherhood.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFive%20weeks%20after%20they%20were%20born%2C%20I%20brought%20two%20babies%20home%2C%20leaving%20my%20one%20child%20who%20needed%20more%20support%20in%20the%20hospital.%20This%20is%20the%20point%20where%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkid-free-vacation-mom-guilt-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Emom%20guilt%20set%20in%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20for%20the%20first%20time.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20could%20never%20be%20in%20more%20than%20one%20place%20at%20a%20time.%20If%20I%20was%20feeding%20the%20babies%20at%20home%2C%20I%20wasn't%20feeding%20the%20baby%20in%20the%20hospital.%20There%20was%20never%20enough%20mommy%20to%20go%20around.%20There%20didn't%20seem%20to%20be%20a%20winning%20option%20%E2%80%94%20I%20just%20felt%20I%20was%20always%20letting%20one%20of%20them%20down.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFinally%2C%20at%20nearly%20six%20weeks%2C%20all%20of%20my%20babies%20were%20home.%20My%20husband%20and%20I%20were%20new%20to%20parenting%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsingle-mom-parent-to-teens-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Edidn't%20know%20what%20we%20were%20doing%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20with%20one%20baby%2C%20let%20alone%20three.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b93df8d8-cad8-4bb2-82d0-84bce5af62c6%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EWe%20hired%20help%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWe%20set%20up%20a%20cot%20and%20a%20changing%20station%20downstairs%20and%20upstairs.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFeeds%2C%20a%20combination%20of%20breast%20milk%20and%20formula%2C%20happened%20every%20three%20hours.%20They%20all%20fed%20at%20the%20same%20time.%20I'd%20breastfeed%20one%20while%20the%20other%20two%20fed%20from%20a%20bottle%20in%20their%20bassinet.%20We%20used%20a%20muslin%20blanket%20to%20prop%20the%20bottle%20in%20place%20for%20the%20two%20in%20the%20bassinets%2C%20arranging%20that%20they%20could%20turn%20away%20when%20they%20didn't%20want%20anymore.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20had%20huge%20amounts%20of%20anxiety%20around%20feed%20times.%20Whenever%20someone%20wanted%20to%20visit%2C%20I%20tried%20to%20make%20sure%20they%20came%20during%20a%20feed%20so%20I%20wasn't%20doing%20it%20alone.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFrom%20a%20very%20early%20age%2C%20we%20had%20a%20strict%20bedtime%20routine%20and%20overnight%20schedule%20%E2%80%94%20something%20suggested%20by%20a%20maternity%20nurse%20we%20hired%20to%20help%20us%20for%20a%20week%20when%20we%20all%20arrived%20home.%20We%20were%20militant%20and%20inflexible%20because%20anything%20that%20would%20give%20us%20a%20minute%20more%20sleep%20was%20worth%20doing.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWe%20tried%20to%20keep%20them%20all%20on%20the%20same%20schedule%20overnight%2C%20which%20meant%20when%20one%20woke%20up%20for%20a%20feeding%2C%20we%20fed%20them%20all.%20Otherwise%2C%20we'd%20be%20getting%20one%20back%20to%20sleep%20just%20as%20another%20woke.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThose%20moments%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20night%2C%20when%20I%20was%20just%20exhausted%20and%20wanted%20to%20sleep%20%E2%80%94%20I%20felt%20like%20I%20was%20going%20to%20break.%20I%20remember%20times%20when%20one%20would%20roll%20over%20or%20whack%20each%20other%20in%20the%20face%2C%20waking%20everyone%20up%20%E2%80%94%20it%20was%20soul-destroying.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c96efe52-fc3a-45eb-b94f-ecd5b2445dae%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20needed%206%20figures%20to%20cover%20the%20costs%20of%20day%20care%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOne%20of%20our%20best%20decisions%20was%20to%20hire%20a%20nanny%20to%20come%20in%20from%206%20a.m.%20to%209%20a.m.%20a%20few%20mornings%20a%20week.%20That%20way%20I%20knew%2C%20even%20if%20I%20had%20a%20terrible%20night%2C%20I%20could%20catch%20up%20on%20sleep%20if%20she%20was%20there.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOnce%20the%20kids%20turned%201%2C%20I%20started%20looking%20at%20the%20possibility%20of%20returning%20to%20work.%20I%20had%20co-founded%20a%20company%20alongside%20my%20brother.%20I%20worked%20out%20that%20I%20would%20have%20to%20make%20at%20least%20%C2%A385%2C000%20(around%20%24109%2C400)%20just%20to%20break%20even%20on%20the%20nursery%20fees.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20I%20know%20a%20lot%20of%20women%20will%20do%20this%20for%20a%20number%20of%20reasons%2C%20I%20decided%20it%20wasn't%20something%20I%20was%20willing%20to%20do.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMy%20career%20had%20been%20an%20integral%20part%20of%20my%20identity%2C%20so%20I%20had%20to%20go%20through%20stages%20of%20grief%20until%20I%20finally%20accepted%20it%20was%20over.%20It%20was%20a%20huge%20cost%20I%20paid%20in%20having%20triplets.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBecause%20we%20live%20in%20the%20UK%2C%20we%20qualified%20for%2015%20hours%20of%20free%20childcare%20in%20September%202024%20when%20the%20babies%20were%202.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20using%20the%20time%20for%20exercise%20and%20%3Cspan%3Ebuilding%20a%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.leilagreen.com%2Fmama-mag%3Ffbclid%3DPAZXh0bgNhZW0CMTEAAaZJ1aVa_8xIfNzmArR6TQsOVBbOASZAlIosF1VPLGq8_IPDtkocADR_FaQ_aem_DJ0wSJU_HTMZ-Lq3E9QeqA%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Enew%20brand%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20%26quot%3BF***%20Mum%20Guilt%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20will%20host%20events%20for%20moms%20about%3C%2Fspan%3E%20mom%20guilt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20has%20been%20amazing%20to%20have%20the%20time%20and%20brain%20space%20to%20think%20about%20and%20build%20a%20brand%20from%20scratch%20%E2%80%94%20to%20have%20time%20to%20do%20something%20for%20me%20and%20other%20moms.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENow%20that%20they%20are%20todd