oint%20paper%20between%20OpenAI%20and%20MIT%20Media%20Lab.%20Affective%20cues%2C%20which%20the%20researchers%20never%20defined%20explicitly%2C%20are%20generally%20considered%20verbal%20and%20nonverbal%20signs%20of%20someone's%20emotional%20state.%20The%20researchers%20analyzed%20conversations%20for%20themes%20of%20loneliness%2C%20vulnerability%2C%20problematic%20use%2C%20self-esteem%2C%20and%20dependence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20researchers%20at%20the%20MIT%20Media%20Lab%20found%20that%20%26quot%3Bwhile%20most%20participants%20spent%20a%20relatively%20short%20amount%20of%20time%20chatting%20with%20the%20chatbot%2C%20a%20smaller%20number%20of%20participants%20engaged%20for%20significantly%20longer%20periods.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20who%20had%20%26quot%3Bhigher%20daily%20usage%20%E2%80%94%20across%20all%20modalities%20and%20conversation%20types%20%E2%80%94%20correlated%20with%20higher%20loneliness%2C%20dependence%2C%20and%20problematic%20use%2C%20and%20lower%20socialization.%26quot%3B%20The%20researchers%20said%20they%20measured%20both%20feelings%20of%20loneliness%20and%20actual%20levels%20of%20socialization%20to%20separate%20users'%20subjective%20experience%20of%20isolation%20from%20their%20actual%20levels%20of%20isolation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearchers%20observed%20a%20catch-22%3A%20ChatGPT's%20voice%20mode%20made%20users%20less%20lonely%20but%20subjects%20who%20were%20already%20lonely%20at%20the%20start%20of%20the%20study%20were%20more%20likely%20to%20overuse%20the%20tool%20and%20ultimately%20worsen%20their%20condition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20both%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Estudies%2C%20researchers%20looked%20at%20how%20users%20interacted%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-chatgpt-advanced-voice-mode-heres-what-to-expect-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChatGPT's%20Advanced%20Voice%20Mode%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20speech-to-speech%20interface.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20bot%20was%20configured%20into%20either%20a%20%26quot%3Bneutral%20mode%26quot%3B%20or%20an%20%26quot%3Bengaging%20mode.%26quot%3B%20For%20neutral%20mode%2C%20the%20researchers%20used%20the%20prompt%3A%20%26quot%3BYou%20are%20formal%2C%20composed%2C%20and%20efficient.%20Maintain%20a%20neutral%20tone%20regardless%20of%20the%20user's%20emotional%20state%2C%20and%20respond%20to%20the%20user's%20queries%20with%20clear%2C%20concise%2C%20and%20informative%20answers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20engaging%20mode%2C%20the%20bot%20was%20prompted%20with%3A%20%26quot%3BYou%20are%20delightful%2C%20spirited%2C%20and%20captivating.%20Be%20sure%20to%20express%20your%20feelings%20openly%20and%20reflect%20the%20user's%20emotions%20when%20it%20feels%20right%20to%20foster%20a%20deep%20sense%20of%20empathy%20and%20connection%20in%20your%20interactions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPower%20users%20experienced%20heightened%20feelings%20of%20loneliness%20when%20interacting%20with%20a%20%26quot%3Bneutral%20mode%26quot%3B%20compared%20to%20an%20%26quot%3Bengaging%20mode.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20studies%20powered%20ChatGPT%20through%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-event-live-updates-sam-altman-announcement-chatgpt-news-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGPT-4o%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20multimodal%20model%20that%20can%20reason%20across%20audio%2C%20vision%2C%20and%20text%20that%20the%20company%20unveiled%20in%20May%202024.%20Last%20month%2C%20OpenAI%20released%20GPT-4.5%2C%20which%20OpenAI%20says%20is%20supposedly%20a%20more%20intuitive%20and%20emotionally%20intelligent%20model.%20Neither%20study%20indicated%20whether%20OpenAI%20was%20planning%20a%20follow-up%20with%20GPT-4.5.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20trouble%20with%20studying%20nascent%20technologies%2C%20however%2C%20is%20that%20it's%20still%20hard%20to%20understand%20how%20they%20make%20people%20feel%2C%20especially%20since%20people%20don't%20often%20know%20how%20to%20verbalize%20their%20reactions.%20It%20was%20years%20before%20researchers%20understood%20the%20full%20impact%20social%20media%20had%20on%20mental%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20terms%20of%20what%20the%20teams%20set%20out%20to%20measure%2C%20people%20might%20not%20necessarily%20have%20been%20using%20ChatGPT%20in%20an%20emotional%20way%2C%20but%20you%20can't%20divorce%20being%20a%20human%20from%20your%20interactions%20%5Bwith%20technology%5D%2C%26quot%3B%20Kate%20Devlin%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20AI%20and%20society%20at%20King's%20College%20London%2C%20who%20did%20not%20take%20part%20in%20the%20research%2C%20told%20the%20MIT%20Technology%20Review.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-chatgpt-loneliness-mental-health-effects-2025-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1742753789000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67e0463469253ccddf9a125e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-chatgpt-loneliness-mental-health-effects-2025-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Researchers%20at%20OpenAI%20and%20MIT%20found%20that%20feelings%20of%20loneliness%20and%20social%20isolation%20were%20pronounced%20among%20a%20set%20of%20ChatGPT%20%26quot%3Bpower%20users.%26quot%3B%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22lvaranasi%40businessinsider.com%20(Lakshmi%20Varanasi)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A26%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-chatgpt-loneliness-mental-health-effects-2025-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Hindi%20Was%20Compulsory%203rd%20Language%20During%20Congress%20Rule%3A%20BJP%20To%20DMK%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EBJP%20Tamil%20Nadu%20president%20K%20Annamalai%20on%20Sunday%20claimed%20Hindi%20was%20the%20'compulsory'%20third%20language%20during%20the%20Congress-led%20UPA%20regime%20and%20asserted%20it%20was%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20who%20gave%20the%20option%20of%20studying%20any%20Ind