0restaurant%2C%20created%20in%201990%20in%20Bengaluru%2C%20which%20went%20on%20to%20be%20featured%20among%20the%20World%E2%80%99s%20Best%20Restaurants.%20Then%20came%20the%20London-based%20%E2%80%98Bombay%20Brasserie%E2%80%99%2C%20which%20he%20started%20in%201982%20%E2%80%94%20the%20venture%20helped%20Parsi%2C%20Gujarati%2C%20and%20Maharashtrian%20fare%20find%20their%20footing%20among%20epicurean%20choices%20%E2%80%94%20followed%20by%20Quilon%20in%201999.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ERetaining%20the%20glint%20of%20the%20MICHELIN%20Star%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChef%20Sriram%E2%80%99s%20tables%20have%20seen%20the%20likes%20of%20former%20prime%20ministers%20Atal%20Bihari%20Vajpayee%20and%20Dr%20Manmohan%20Singh%2C%20Sir%20John%20Major%2C%20Prince%20Charles%2C%20Roger%20Federer%2C%20AR%20Rahman%2C%20Sunil%20Gavaskar%2C%20Tom%20Cruise%2C%20and%20Madonna%2C%20among%20other%20national%20and%20international%20celebrities.%20He%20is%20also%20the%20only%20Indian%20chef%20to%20have%20cooked%20at%20the%20World%20Economic%20Forum%20in%20Davos%20continuously%20for%20the%20past%2016%20years.%20He%20says%20he%20owes%20his%20success%20to%20the%20holy%20triad%20%E2%80%94%20the%20right%20technique%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F268194%2Fgujju-ben-na-nasta-mumbai-best-breakfast-inspiring-woman-entrepreneur-grandmother-india%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eauthentic%20ingredients%2C%20and%20passion%20for%20the%20craft%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F03%2Fquilon-south-indian-food-3-1742212089.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Bold%20flavours%20and%20succulent%20meats%20form%20the%20basis%20of%20the%20Quilon%20menu%20in%20London%2C%20winning%20it%20a